The brief introduction by Carmelianus (if it was indeed written by him) seems to favour the side of the Venetians in the quarrel. The designation of “quam elegantissimae'' given to the six epistles in the colophon will not be endorsed by Latin scholars of the present age.

It should be noticed that the first, third, and fourth of these letters have been recently published.
